   <body>
      <p>Power Invoice Generation for Salesforce Billing is a Power product that works exclusively with Salesforce Billing. It allows Salesforce Billing customers to customize and export invoices, statements, and receipts that provide a free and powerful way to generate documents.</p>
      <p>What's in the Package?</p>
      <p>The Power Invoice Generation for Salesforce Billing package includes:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>Power Invoice Generation</li>
         <li>Power Batch. For more information, refer to <xref href="https://documentation.Power.com/display/COMPOSER/.Power+Batch+vWinter-20"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external">
               <u>Power Batch</u>
            </xref> product documentation.</li>
         <li>Power Trigger. For more information, refer to <xref href="https://documentation.Power.com/display/COMPOSER/.Power+Trigger+vWinter-20"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external">
               <u>Power Trigger</u>
            </xref> product documentation.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>What are the Limitations?</p>
      <p>Power Invoice Generation for Salesforce Billing includes all of the features and functionality of Power Composer with the following exceptions:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>Customers can only generate documents from the objects within the Salesforce Billing installed package (those with the blng prefix).</li>
         <li>Word and HTML Email are the only supported template types.</li>
         <li>Email and PDF are the only output file types.</li>
         <li>Up to 1,000 free invoices per month.</li>
      </ul>
